    <slide title="Story Types" layout="normal">
        <div class="left">
        <img class="scale" src="/pix/agile_demo/tracker21.png"/>
        </div>
        <div class="right">
            <p>These identify the type of work in a task</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Feature</li>
                <li>Bug</li>
                <li>Chore</li>
                <li>Milestone</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </slide>
    <slide title="Story Points" layout="normal">
        <div class="left">
        <img class="scale" src="/pix/agile_demo/tracker22.png"/>
        </div>
        <div class="right">
            <p>These identify the "size" of a task</p>
            <ul>
                <li>0 for bugs, milestones</li>
                <li>1 for &lt; 4 hours</li>
                <li>2 for ~ 1 day</li>
                <li>3 for ~ 2 days</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </slide>
    <slide title="Velocity" layout="normal">
        <div class="left">
        <img class="scale" src="/pix/agile_demo/tracker23.png"/>
        </div>
        <div class="right">
            <p>Story points are used to calculate velocity</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Team velocity per iteration</li>
                <li>Member pair: 4 points x 4 days = 16 points</li>
                <li>Add 20% buffer </li>
                <li>Leads to expected 20 points per team pair per iteration:
                *this* is what the backlog + current tasks should add up 
                to at the beginning of an iteration</li>
                <li>Tracker will adjust</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </slide>

